Description: Supportal (an app) enables people who are coping with health problems to instantly connect with each other on anonymous phone calls.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Supportal (an app) is a portal for peer-to-peer support that enables people who are coping with difficult health problems (e.g., cancer, infertility, HIV, addiction, combat PTSD) to connect on anonymous phone calls with similarly situated people at the push of a button. Here’s how Supportal works: (1) a user joins a group that fits his/her circumstances (e.g., addiction, cancer, infertility, etc.); (2) the user presses the “Make a Call” button from the group page, which connects him/her to an outside conference line; (3) once a call is initiated, other group members receive a push notification, alerting them that someone from their group is waiting to talk; (4) the first group member to press the push notification is connected to the same conference line where the initial caller is waiting to talk; (5) because users call into an outside conference line, neither caller can see the other’s phone number, so the conversation is anonymous. Supportal’s goal is to help people help each other.
Founders: Marisa Lee, Mark Schottinger, Porter Littlepage

Description: InfraRed Rx is a biotechnology company that develops non-invasive tools to measure oxygen delivery and use in muscle.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: InfraRed Rx is a biotechnology company that develops non-invasive tools to measure oxygen delivery and use in muscle. Its technology relies on how active muscles use mitochondria to turn oxygen into energy. InfraRed Rx tools use near-infrared spectroscopy to assess mitochondrial health and function. This reveals broader information about a patient’s health and fitness and can shed light on a variety of health conditions. Peripheral artery disease (PAD) is one such condition. InfraRed Rx is particularly focused on PAD, in which blood vessels in a patient’s leg build up plaque, making it harder for blood to flow during exercise. This causes leg pain during physical activities such as walking. InfraRed Rx has developed a non-invasive technology to improve treatments for PAD. The company also provides services such as data processing and analysis, clinical guidance, and consulting.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: A regional manufacturer of architectural, commercial and industrial coatings for the professional and do-it-yourself markets.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: M.A.B. Paints, now in its 102nd year, enjoys a legacy built by the hard work and determination of four generations of the Bruder family. Founded in 1899 when Michael A. Bruder opened the first M.A.B. Paints store in South Philadelphia, M.A.B. quickly established a reputation for quality products and superior customer service. Michael pioneered pre-mixed paints in his trading area, an innovation that garnered M.A.B. a loyal following of professional users. In the early part of the century, Michael expanded M.A.B.’s reach, opening new stores throughout the Philadelphia area. Following the death of Michael A. Bruder in 1932, Michael’s son Thomas A. Bruder took control of the company and continued to oversee its growth. By 1939, there were 13 stores in the region. During Tom’s reign, he made his father’s dream a reality and left behind a vital and growing company. Thomas A. Bruder, Jr. succeeded his father as President of M.A.B. in 1967. Under Tom Jr.’s direction, many new products were introduced and field sales service teams were established to provide information and guidance to builders, architects and contractors in the rapidly evolving paint industry. In 1969, M.A.B. Paints purchased the Smith-Alsop Paint Company, adding new locations in six midwestern states, Alabama, and Florida. Throughout the 1970s, 1980s and 1990s, M.A.B. continued to expand its geographic reach with new stores in new markets servicing legions of new professional and do-it-yourself customers.
